<subSubSection id="2AAD1097FFE5FFB3CEABF991FDF1FEDA" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1290" pageId="4" pageNumber="1289" type="description">
<paragraph id="6208431CFFE5FFB3CEABF991FDF1FEDA" blockId="4.[178,1085,1548,1599]" lastBlockId="5.[178,1085,219,328]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1290" pageId="4" pageNumber="1289">
C o m m e n t: The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="A5B7389FFFE5FFB2CC95F990FCE4F9B0" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1982" box="[652,781,1549,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amisensis">
<emphasis id="50C39F0EFFE5FFB2CC95F990FCE4F9B0" box="[652,781,1549,1570]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1289">L. amisensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a single female [sic] from &quot; 
<collectingCountry id="1AA0038CFFE5FFB2CF31F9B4FE94F9AD" box="[296,381,1577,1599]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="1289">Turquie</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="A0738DFEFFE5FFB2CF91F9B4FE33F9AD" box="[392,474,1577,1599]" country="Turkey" name="Samsun" pageId="4" pageNumber="1289">Samsun</collectingRegion>
, Samsun-Kavak&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="06263EEDFFE5FFB2CC83F9B4FCF8F9AD" author="PACE R" box="[666,785,1577,1599]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1289" pagination="579 - 594" refId="ref11005" refString="PACE R. (1982): Leptusa raccolte dal Dr Claude Besuchet nella Penisola Iberica, nella regione balcanica, in Turchia e in estremo oriente (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue suisse de Zoologie 89: 579 - 594." type="journal article" year="1982">PACE 1982</bibRefCitation>
). Although similar in colora- tion and other external characters to 
<taxonomicName id="A5B7389FFFE4FFB3CC22FF41FD32FF62" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2009" box="[571,731,219,241]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ionopolitana">
<emphasis id="50C39F0EFFE4FFB3CC22FF41FD32FF62" box="[571,731,219,241]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1290">L. ionopolitana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and also geographically close, it seems to represent a distinct species, as is suggested by the different shape of the spermatheca (
<figureCitation id="FA8C5F99FFE4FFB3CF0DFE88FE88FEB9" box="[276,353,277,299]" captionStart="Figs 49-54" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1491,1511]" captionTargetBox="[186,1079,879,1436]" captionTargetId="figure-319@16.[178,1084,873,1476]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 49-54: Leptusa ionopolitana PACE (49-51), L. amisensis PACE (52), and L. sengleti PACE (53- 54): (49, 53) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (50-52) spermatheca; (54) male sternite VII. Scale bars: 54: 0.2 mm; 49-53: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276633/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
). Males from the 
<typeStatus id="BD0CFDBEFFE4FFB3CC0CFE8BFDA8FEB9" box="[533,577,278,299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1290">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation id="FA8C5F99FFE4FFB3CCB8FE88FD0CFEB9" box="[673,741,277,299]" captionStart="Map 2" captionStartId="4.[178,223,652,672]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,628]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[178,1085,212,628]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Map 2: Distributions of four species of the subgenus Stictopisalia in northern Turkey, based on revised records: Leptusa ionopolitana PACE (open circles), L. fibula ASSING (filled circles), L. amisensis PACE (open square), and L. flagellulifera nov.sp. (filled squares)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276617/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1290">Map 2</figureCitation>
) or its vicinity would be required to clarify the status of 
<taxonomicName id="A5B7389FFFE4FFB3CF8CFEAEFDFBFEDA" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1982" box="[405,530,307,328]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amisensis">
<emphasis id="50C39F0EFFE4FFB3CF8CFEAEFDFBFEDA" box="[405,530,307,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1290">L. amisensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
